The paper deals with the problem of finding the shortest transformation between two configurations of tokens on the edges of a graph, which can be seen as a reconfiguration problem. This problem is related to graph theory, combinatorics, and algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.GT (Discrete Mathematics), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) due to the use of approximation algorithms and parameterized complexity.
